_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_

**Stream the request body under the size cap.**

When `Content-Length` is missing or understated, this path still does `ReadToEndAsync()` and only enforces `MaxBackupSizeBytes` after the whole payload is buffered as a string. A chunked upload can therefore blow past the 10 MB guardrail and only get rejected after the memory cost is already paid.



<details>
<summary>Suggested direction</summary>

```diff
-            string json;
+            string json;
             try
             {
-                using var reader = new StreamReader(
-                    Request.Body,
-                    Encoding.UTF8,
-                    detectEncodingFromByteOrderMarks: true,
-                    leaveOpen: false);
-                json = await reader.ReadToEndAsync().ConfigureAwait(false);
+                await using var buffer = new MemoryStream();
+                var chunk = new byte[16 * 1024];
+                long totalBytes = 0;
+                int read;
+
+                while ((read = await Request.Body.ReadAsync(chunk, 0, chunk.Length, RequestAborted).ConfigureAwait(false)) > 0)
+                {
+                    totalBytes += read;
+                    if (totalBytes > BackupService.MaxBackupSizeBytes)
